			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As we all know, recieving a blob the size of 64k blob and up crashes the bot.
<br />

<br />
As funcom dont want to do anything about it, lets try to make a solution for it in stead.
<br />

<br />
Isnt there a way for aochat to ignore a packet if its too big, or simply not recieve it? Or get the size of a packet, if its too big, pretend like it recieved it.
<br />

<br />
I've been looking through the socket commands. But i cant seem to find anything. And i fear that the ao server simply disconnects bots, no matter what we do.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
