			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The solution so far has been to make all the bot-types cap and/or split out-blobs at around 20-25K size and pause between them.
<br />

<br />
The other solution has been to let bots rebounce when LD'ed.
<br />

<br />
Allthough that takes care of a alot, there are some times lag on the server itself collects up packets and then returns them as one single large packet to the target instead of multiples, resulting in a crash/LD.
<br />

<br />
Last time i talked with Jesper from FC-dev they were working on it and planned to do something about the collecting of packets problem, but thats 7-8 months ago now.
<br />

<br />
I doubt there's any way to avoid it on the recieverside, as the disconnection happens from the serverside in those instances, not on the clientside, atleast that's what Jesper told me. In other words the problem must be fixed serverside to be a 100% idiot-proof solution.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
